{"id": "1514028589043941479", "channel_id": "1514028589043941479", "author_id": "211066372061396992", "author_name": "strawberryflux", "content": "(Before I begin: I'm a player from Korea, and this post was written using a translator.)\n(Since the translator may mistranslate, I've noted the English terms in parentheses for the key keywords.)\n\n\n\nI was one of the players who was thrilled about the Saya collaboration and had high hopes for it.\n\nI've experimented with Saya across several party setups, and I'm currently trying to build a party around her together with Corposant.\n\nThe reason I'm making this post is that, compared to other Awakeners, Saya feels like she lacks personality and isn't very fun to play.\n\n\n\nThe first reason, I suspect, is that the Corrosion on her 0-cost skill (Viscera Blossoms) is simply too strong.\n\nEven though Viscera Blossoms has a discard effect, it produces no Aftershock on other cards, so there's no synergy. And her 2-cost skill (Biomimicry) has far lower values than other Awakeners with similar skills.\n\nSong of Saya is hard to trigger because Saya's Base Aliemus is 200. To gain Aliemus, you have to go through a complicated process — using Rouse, then activating Crimson Furnace to use a skill that has Perception Warp applied — and because of the nature of the Perception Warp effect, this process can sometimes become a very unpleasant experience.\n\nOn top of that, while Crimson Furnace serves both as a means of healing and as a way to gain Aliemus, its 3-turn cooldown forces you to pick only one of the two, which also makes it hard to Gain Aliemus.\n\nSaya even has Sigil Yield scaling, which is a less useful stat compared to other Awakeners. This stat is far less directly helpful in combat than others, and in some battles it's completely useless.\n\n\n(I had more to say than fits in one post, so I've continued in the replies below.)\n\n<@&1166257943742787615>", "timestamp": "2026-06-09T22:09:04.919000+00:00", "thread_id": "1514028589043941479", "reactions": [{"emoji": "Celeste_agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 13}, {"emoji": "Saya_yum", "emoji_id": "1513124263291387975", "count": 1}], "attachments": [{"id": "1514028592185737296", "filename": "saya.png", "content_type": "image/webp", "size": 131028, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1514028589043941479/1514028592185737296/saya.png?ex=6a2a8941&is=6a2937c1&hm=6b93b123a051c87900d49d6c706860b4cc7cc51240edd503888e792376574ced&"}]}
{"id": "1514028808083079280", "channel_id": "1514028589043941479", "author_id": "211066372061396992", "author_name": "strawberryflux", "content": "The second reason is that I wonder whether all of these problems with Saya stem from the developers valuing Gynoecium too highly.\n\nThe Embryo Fusion value on her 2-cost skill (Biomimicry) is about average, but it has no effect other than producing Gynoecium. Even her Absolute Axiom effect, aside from recovering 50 Aliemus when Crimson Furnace is activated once every 3 turns, does nothing more than grant 1 stack of Gynoecium.\n\nIf the Absolute Axiom effect were too strong, it could certainly create balance problems. But as it stands, this effect seems to exist solely for the sake of Gynoecium, and that is a very \"unfun\" design.\n\nIn practice, using Biomimicry frequently to obtain Gynoecium puts a corresponding strain on the party, and without Dream of Medicine, even that isn't easy.\n\nAnd even the silver key effect that was added with this story release doesn't do much aside from Gynoecium. What's worse, the 2 cards granted by the silver key carry a Perception Warp effect, so there's a chance you won't even be able to use them.\n\nGynoecium has no effect except when using Song of Saya. But for an Awakener who struggles even to gain Aliemus, these effects sacrificed for the sake of Gynoecium only lower Saya's fun factor, and I believe they're exactly what makes her hard to use for anything other than applying the Corrosion debuff.", "timestamp": "2026-06-09T22:09:57.142000+00:00", "thread_id": "1514028589043941479"}
{"id": "1514028830342381731", "channel_id": "1514028589043941479", "author_id": "211066372061396992", "author_name": "strawberryflux", "content": "Honestly, if she had simply been an Awakener specialized purely in Corrosion, I wouldn't have these complaints. The disappointing part is that Saya is incredibly charming, and she isn't a character who should be reduced to merely a tool for applying a single debuff to enemies.\n\nMy very first visual novel was \"Saya no Uta.\" I know that the Morimens developers love Saya no Uta, and I love Saya too — and even more than that (perhaps as much as the developers love Saya no Uta), I love the game Morimens itself.\n\nSo I'd really like to know what the developers had in mind when designing Saya's skills, and what their goal was in creating her.\n\nAnd this is a small wish, but if the developers also recognize these points and there's some room for improvement, I hope Saya can become an Awakener who doesn't leave players feeling \"isn't she pretty much useless outside of Corrosion?\" — one who is a little more loved by the Keepers.\n\nThank you for taking your valuable time to read this long post.", "timestamp": "2026-06-09T22:10:02.449000+00:00", "thread_id": "1514028589043941479", "edited_timestamp": "2026-06-09T22:10:46.313000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 4}]}
